Wall Street    Right time to invest? – Helix Energy Solutions Group, Inc. (HLX), Achillion...
Wall Street

Right time to invest? – Helix Energy Solutions Group, Inc. (HLX), Achillion Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (ACHN)

By Grady Hoffman -   July 25, 2017 



 








Share on Facebook
Tweet on Twitter










Shares of Helix Energy Solutions Group, Inc. (NYSE:HLX) are on a recovery track as they have regained 22.61% since bottoming out at $4.82 on May. 31, 2017. Thanks to a rise of almost 3.5% in the past five days, the stock price is now down -32.99% so far on the year — still in weak territory. In this case, shares are down -50.21% from $11.87 , the 52-week high touched on Dec. 06, 2016, but are collecting gains at -25.47% for the past 12 months.
HLX Target Price Reaches $9.13
 Brokerage houses, on average, are recommending investors to buy Helix Energy Solutions Group, Inc. (HLX)’s shares projecting a $9.13 target price. Analysts‟ target price forecasts are a prediction of a stock‟s future price, generally over the 12 months following the release date (Asquith et al., 2005). This forecast is a point estimate that provides investors with a benchmark against which to directly compare stock price in the short run.Target prices made by analysts employed by large brokers, who have access to a greater resource pool, are more likely to be met over the 12-month forecast period.
 How Quickly Helix Energy Solutions Group, Inc. (HLX)’s Sales Declined?
 HLX’s revenue has declined at an average annualized rate of about -7% during the past five years. However, the company’s most recent quarter increase of 14.8% looks attractive. The sales growth rate for a stock is a measure of how the stock’s sales per share (SPS) has grown over a specific period of time. It tells an investor how quickly a company is increasing its revenues. The sales growth rate helps investors determine how strong the overall growth-orientation is for a stock or portfolio.
Achillion Pharmaceuticals, Inc. Achieves Below-Average Profit Margin 





  The best measure of a company is its profitability, for without it, it cannot grow, and if it doesn’t grow, then its stock will trend downward. Increasing profits are the best indication that a company can pay dividends and that the share price will trend upward. Creditors will loan money at a cheaper rate to a profitable company than to an unprofitable one; consequently, profitable companies can use leverage to increase stockholders’ equity even more. Profitability ratios compare different accounts to see how efficiently a business is generating profits. These ratios show how well income is generated through operations, and are important to both creditors and investors. They help determine the company’s ability to continue operating. Currently, Helix Energy Solutions Group, Inc. net profit margin for the 12 months is at -13.98%. Comparatively, the peers have a net margin -13.8%, and the sector’s average is 79.87%. In that light, it seems in weak position compared to its peers and sector. The profit margin measures the amount of net income earned with each dollar’s worth of revenue. It shows the percentage of sales that remain after all of the company’s expenses have been paid. The higher the ratio, the better.
 Achillion Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (NASDAQ:ACHN) is another stock that is grabbing investors attention these days. Its shares have trimmed -55.03% since hitting a peak level of $9.49 on Aug. 24, 2016. Meanwhile, due to a recent pullback which led to a fall of almost -0.7% in the past one month, the stock price is now outperforming with 3.39% so far on the year — still in weak zone. In this case, shares are 35.56% higher from $3.15, the worst price in 52 weeks suffered on Apr. 24, 2017, and are keeping their losses at 4.91% for the past six months.
Analysts See Achillion Pharmaceuticals, Inc. 2.48% Above Current Levels 
 The good news is there’s still room for Achillion Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (ACHN) to grow. At recent closing price of $4.27, ACHN has a chance to add $2.48 or 58.08% in 52 weeks, based on mean target price ($6.75) placed by analysts.The analyst consensus opinion of 1.8 looks like a buy. It has a 36-month beta of 1.95 , so you might be in for a bumpy ride.
 Are Achillion Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (NASDAQ:ACHN) Earnings Growing Rapidly?
 For the past 5 years, Achillion Pharmaceuticals, Inc.’s EPS growth has been nearly 8.1%. Sure, the percentage is encouraging but better times are ahead as looking out over a next 5-year period, analysts expect the company to see its earnings go up by 17.58%, annually.
Is ACHN Turning Profits into Returns?
 Achillion Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (ACHN)’s ROE is -15.61%, while industry’s is -9.29%. The average ROE for the sector stands at -7.95%. The return on equity (ROE), also known as return on investment (ROI), is the best measure of the return, since it is the product of the operating performance, asset turnover, and debt-equity management of the firm. If a firm can borrow money and use it to achieve a higher return than the cost of the debt, then the leveraging creates additional revenue that accrues to stockholders as increased equity.
 Achillion Pharmaceuticals, Inc.’s ROA is -15.16%, while industry’s average is -5.27%. As with any return, the higher this number the better. However, it, too, needs to be taken into the context of a company’s peer group as well as its sector. The average return on assets for companies in the same sector is -16.98. The return on assets (ROA) (aka return on total assets, return on average assets), is one of the most widely used profitability ratios because it is related to both profit margin and asset turnover, and shows the rate of return for both creditors and investors of the company. ROA shows how well a company controls its costs and utilizes its resources.












 


